==English==

===Etymology===
From the concept of [[martyrdom]] through [[fire]].

===Alternative spellings===
* '''baptism of fire'''

===Noun===
'''baptism by fire''' (''plural:'' '''[[baptisms by fire]]''')
# A [[rite of passage]] through the [[survival]] or [[sucess]] of a [[crisis]].
# A trying [[ordeal]] that was not [[experience]]d before.
# A change in [[initial]] [[attitude]] or [[ideal]]s through a [[traumatic]] situation.

